description.narrative: Health facilities have strengthened capacity to provide quality preventive and curative nutrition services in a sustainable way, including in humanitarian situations.,which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children, adolescents and women, especially the most vulnerable and those affected by shocks, have increased access to and the utilization of promotional, preventive and curative nutrition services.

description.narrative: In 2019, integrated management of severe acute malnutrition continued to be provided nationwide through the health system and treated 414,239 children (109% of the national target covering the period January to December 2019). Performance indicators met minimum standards with cure, death and defaulter rates of 90.2%, 1.4% and 5.0% respectively. Vitamin A and deworming campaigns were conducted nationwide in 2019 however, more sustainable approaches need to be explored. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
